WEBVTT

00:05.353 --> 00:07.920
Anna, I love you.

00:07.964 --> 00:09.792
We're done.

00:09.835 --> 00:12.360
[ Knock on door ] Previously on
"A Million Little Things"...

00:12.403 --> 00:14.579
I never should have gone
to France.

00:14.623 --> 00:16.581
Everything got messed up.

00:16.625 --> 00:19.410
I want you to screen
your documentary here.

00:19.454 --> 00:22.587
I think it's exactly what
the student body needs to see.

00:22.631 --> 00:26.026
Mr. Dennings, I succeeded
in spite of this place,

00:26.069 --> 00:27.027
not because of it.

00:27.070 --> 00:28.854
You should be ashamed
of yourself.

00:28.898 --> 00:31.205
What I care about is
how much she's drinking.

00:31.248 --> 00:32.684
Eddie: She's at a party.

00:32.728 --> 00:34.860
And the guy she's here with
is an alcoholic.

00:36.645 --> 00:38.777
There's something
I haven't told you.

00:38.821 --> 00:39.865
I'm married.

00:42.085 --> 00:43.826
We should just
move back in together.

00:43.869 --> 00:47.003
♪♪

00:47.047 --> 00:48.831
I think we should
have a baby.

00:51.181 --> 00:53.531
Eddie: Guys, it's my treat,
so go big.

00:53.575 --> 00:56.447
Wow. I should have lumps removed
more often.[ Chuckles ]

00:56.491 --> 00:57.883
Yeah, I'm kind of
jealous.

00:57.927 --> 01:00.321
Maybe I should start,
I don't know, smoking a lot?

01:00.364 --> 01:01.713
[ Chuckles ]
That's a long game.

01:01.757 --> 01:03.106
I admire the commitment.

01:03.150 --> 01:04.412
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

01:04.455 --> 01:07.067
Well, yes, this dinner
is partially to celebrate

01:07.110 --> 01:08.677
Gary's all-clear,
but it's also celebrating

01:08.720 --> 01:10.896
you two moving in
with each other,

01:10.940 --> 01:14.683
coupled with my getting paid
an obscene amount of money

01:14.726 --> 01:16.554
at this autograph convention
tomorrow.

01:16.598 --> 01:18.208
Yeah, me and all
the other fading rock stars

01:18.252 --> 01:19.296
are cashing in.

01:19.340 --> 01:20.732
No, no, no.
He is downplaying it.

01:20.776 --> 01:22.734
The organizers begged him
to be there.

01:22.778 --> 01:26.390
My boyfriend is a huge get.
Tell everyone you know.

01:26.434 --> 01:28.131
Dropping the B-word --
I like that.

01:28.175 --> 01:29.176
Mm-hmm.

01:29.219 --> 01:30.960
And I would like
to make a toast.

01:31.003 --> 01:33.136
[ Clears throat ]

01:33.180 --> 01:35.573
To my friend, Edward.

01:37.358 --> 01:39.011
I love you, man.

01:39.055 --> 01:41.057
You forgot to undercut it
with a joke at my expense.

01:41.101 --> 01:42.450
[ Chuckles ]No, no.

01:42.493 --> 01:44.887
In the last night
of us living together,

01:44.930 --> 01:47.063
you are going to get
a rare glimpse

01:47.107 --> 01:49.109
at, uh...

01:49.152 --> 01:50.893
sentimental Gary.

01:50.936 --> 01:52.851
Everyone, proceed cautiously.
Don't spook him.

01:53.939 --> 01:55.158
Here's to you, Ed.

01:55.202 --> 01:56.551
Cheers.

01:56.594 --> 01:57.856
Cheers.
Cheers, man.

01:57.900 --> 01:59.206
Genuinely nice.

01:59.249 --> 02:00.294
[ Chuckles ]

02:02.383 --> 02:03.732
Well, Gary,
that was beautiful.

02:03.775 --> 02:05.777
And I have to pee.

02:05.821 --> 02:07.127
I love a woman
who owns it.

02:07.170 --> 02:08.824
You can pop a squat
right past the bar there.

02:08.867 --> 02:10.260
[ Chuckles ]
Thanks.

02:10.304 --> 02:14.221
[ Light jazz music playing ]

02:14.264 --> 02:16.397
Thanks for giving Anna
another chance.

02:16.440 --> 02:18.007
I live for
second chances.

02:18.050 --> 02:19.400
[ Chuckles ]

02:19.443 --> 02:21.793
I like her.
And I love you two together.

02:21.837 --> 02:24.144
And, um,
completely unrelated,

02:24.187 --> 02:26.407
but, uh, I am never
playing on her team

02:26.450 --> 02:27.408
at game night again.

02:27.451 --> 02:29.105
Understandable.
Yeah.

02:29.149 --> 02:31.934
[ Cellphone vibrates ][ Sighs ]

02:31.977 --> 02:34.632
Oh, um, it's Charlie's first day
of preschool.

02:34.676 --> 02:36.068
I'm gonna take this, okay?

02:36.112 --> 02:37.200
Gary: Well, it's duck, duck,
then goose.

02:37.244 --> 02:38.419
But in French.

02:38.462 --> 02:40.203
That was a nice toast.

02:40.247 --> 02:41.639
[ Sighs ]

02:41.683 --> 02:43.424
But as your
new roommate,

02:43.467 --> 02:46.644
I have to remind you that,
like your past roommates,

02:46.688 --> 02:48.820
I am not having sex
with you.

02:48.864 --> 02:50.126
Doctor's orders.

02:50.170 --> 02:51.910
I can't believe we're paying
a fertility doctor

02:51.954 --> 02:53.434
135 bucks a pop

02:53.477 --> 02:55.392
just to tell us
not to have sex.

02:55.436 --> 02:57.351
My dad used to do that
in high school for free.

02:59.266 --> 03:01.355
Do you think they noticed
that I'm not drinking?

03:01.398 --> 03:03.052
Nah.

03:03.095 --> 03:05.054
I just -- I don't want
everyone asking

03:05.097 --> 03:07.274
every five minutes
if we're pregnant yet.

03:07.317 --> 03:09.276
Right.
Less pressure on you.

03:09.319 --> 03:11.234
More pressure on me,
since we're not having sex.

03:11.278 --> 03:12.279
You get it.

03:12.322 --> 03:13.932
But you're not
getting it.

03:13.976 --> 03:16.326
Not until the doctor says so.
[ Chuckles ]

03:17.588 --> 03:19.764
Hi, there. Can I get
a tequila neat, please?

03:19.808 --> 03:20.852
And can you just add it
to my tab?

03:24.291 --> 03:25.814
That's great.

03:25.857 --> 03:32.255
♪♪

03:32.299 --> 03:34.214
Carly?
[ Chuckles ]

03:34.257 --> 03:35.650
Anna, hey.

03:35.693 --> 03:37.347
[ Chuckles ]
It's been so long.

03:37.391 --> 03:39.567
What -- What are you
doing here?

03:39.610 --> 03:41.743
I'm actually
meeting someone.

03:41.786 --> 03:43.527
Oh!
That's nice.

03:43.571 --> 03:45.050
How long
has this been going on?

03:47.009 --> 03:50.099
Hi.
Benoit, party of two.

03:50.142 --> 03:52.014
You...

03:52.057 --> 03:53.537
You're on a date
with Peter?

03:53.581 --> 03:56.671
How could you, after everything
that I told you?

03:56.714 --> 03:58.760
Peter said that stuff
wasn't true.

03:58.803 --> 04:00.936
She posted a podcast
and talked about it.

04:00.979 --> 04:02.111
Carly,
you listened to it.

04:02.154 --> 04:04.505
Yeah, and that podcast
was taken down

04:04.548 --> 04:06.289
because obviously
that girl was lying.

04:06.333 --> 04:07.769
What?

04:08.857 --> 04:09.858
Hello, Anna.

04:12.948 --> 04:14.906
No, it's okay.
Thanks for trying, D.

04:14.950 --> 04:17.126
Just,
when Charlie wakes up,

04:17.169 --> 04:18.997
let her know
Daddy loves her and,

04:19.041 --> 04:20.912
you know, don't eat the crayons.
[ Chuckles ]

04:20.956 --> 04:22.479
Okay.

04:22.523 --> 04:24.394
Really, Peter?
Wow.

04:24.438 --> 04:26.004
Okay.
And so, Sophie Dixon --

04:26.048 --> 04:27.658
was she just
making that all up?

04:29.181 --> 04:31.314
How about Layla Gregory?

04:31.358 --> 04:34.274
'Cause that girl died.

04:34.317 --> 04:37.494
How many other girls were just
"making it up," Peter, huh?

04:38.669 --> 04:39.670
I think
you should go.

04:39.714 --> 04:42.194
Yeah,
I think he's right.

04:43.935 --> 04:45.894
We're here to see
one of my students play.

04:45.937 --> 04:47.199
We're not going
anywhere.

04:47.243 --> 04:49.506
You're kidding.
Your s-- Your student?

04:49.550 --> 04:50.681
You're still teaching?

04:50.725 --> 04:52.335
Maggie: Okay.
Hey, come on.

04:52.379 --> 04:53.597
Let's just go.

04:53.641 --> 04:55.338
What?Let's just go.

04:55.382 --> 04:59.603
♪♪

04:59.647 --> 05:01.083
You look really
familiar to me.

05:01.126 --> 05:03.868
I think I know you
from somewhere.

05:03.912 --> 05:05.957
Wait, it's starting
to come back to me.

05:07.785 --> 05:09.657
[ Whispers ] I'm the guy
that knows where you live.

05:09.700 --> 05:17.926
♪♪

05:23.235 --> 05:24.889
Anna: I should've been
checking in on him.

05:24.933 --> 05:27.675
I mean, how many other girls
is he hurting?

05:29.720 --> 05:31.243
I think I should cancel
my autograph thing tomorrow,

05:31.287 --> 05:32.288
stay with you.

05:32.332 --> 05:34.116
What? No. No.

05:34.159 --> 05:36.466
Well, I'm sure the organizer
only invited me

05:36.510 --> 05:38.120
because, I don't know,

05:38.163 --> 05:40.688
the guys from Chumbawamba
turned it down.

05:40.731 --> 05:42.342
[ Chuckles ]
It's gonna be great.

05:43.908 --> 05:46.171
And honestly...

05:46.215 --> 05:49.000
I could probably use a day
to process.

05:51.133 --> 05:52.874
You sure
you're gonna be okay?

05:52.917 --> 05:53.962
You'll call me
if you need anything?

05:54.005 --> 05:55.964
Yes, I promise.

05:56.007 --> 05:57.182
Alright.

05:57.226 --> 05:59.402
Okay. Thank you.

05:59.446 --> 06:00.534
Have fun tomorrow.

06:00.577 --> 06:01.796
Mm-hmm.

06:04.189 --> 06:05.582
Good night.

06:05.626 --> 06:08.280
♪♪

06:08.324 --> 06:10.282
[ Engine starts ]

06:10.326 --> 06:11.849
♪♪

06:17.333 --> 06:18.943
Hey.

06:18.987 --> 06:21.163
Mm.

06:21.206 --> 06:23.557
You still thinking about
that run-in with Peter?

06:25.559 --> 06:28.170
Last night in this bed
and I spent it

06:28.213 --> 06:32.827
spinning out about that scumbag
the whole time.

06:32.870 --> 06:35.220
Should we postpone the move
until tomorrow?

06:35.264 --> 06:38.920
Give you one more shot
at a perfect last night's sleep?

06:38.963 --> 06:42.445
Or should we give this bed
a proper send-off right now?

06:42.489 --> 06:44.534
Don't. D--
You're just torturing me.

06:44.578 --> 06:46.188
M-Morning breath and all.

06:46.231 --> 06:47.407
[ Chuckles ]

06:47.450 --> 06:49.713
I was just talking about
breakfast in bed.

06:49.757 --> 06:52.020
Oh. Sure.

06:52.063 --> 06:55.023
Will you at least put on a parka
or something over that V-neck

06:55.066 --> 06:56.198
before you come back,
please?

06:56.241 --> 06:57.504
[ Maggie laughs ]

06:57.547 --> 07:00.376
♪♪

07:00.420 --> 07:01.943
Tyrell:
How'd it go with PBS?

07:01.986 --> 07:03.205
Not good.

07:03.248 --> 07:05.120
At the end of the pitch,
the executive said,

07:05.163 --> 07:06.774
"Well told."

07:06.817 --> 07:08.776
That's good, isn't it?
No.

07:08.819 --> 07:11.039
"Well told" is
the kiss of death.

07:11.082 --> 07:13.824
It's the "I think of you
more as a friend" of pitching.

07:13.868 --> 07:15.260
[ Chuckles ]
I guarantee you

07:15.304 --> 07:16.871
my agent's about to call me
and tell me it's a pass.

07:16.914 --> 07:19.264
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

07:19.308 --> 07:20.788
Good luck with that.

07:20.831 --> 07:22.093
I'm gonna see
if Josh has heard

07:22.137 --> 07:23.660
if any colleges posted
their decisions yet.

07:23.704 --> 07:25.096
Alright.

07:25.140 --> 07:28.056
[ Vibrating continues ]

07:28.099 --> 07:30.493
Hey, Dre.
What's up?

07:30.537 --> 07:32.974
The kids can't stop talking
about your documentary.

07:33.017 --> 07:34.454
Thank you.
Means a lot

07:34.497 --> 07:36.717
coming from the vice principal
of Sussex Prep.

07:36.760 --> 07:40.808
Actually, you're talking
to the Dean of Sussex Prep now.

07:40.851 --> 07:42.374
What?

07:42.418 --> 07:43.941
Yeah, Dennings retired.
They gave me his job.

07:43.985 --> 07:46.204
[ Chuckling ] Whoa, man.
Congratulations.

07:46.248 --> 07:48.946
Wait, wait,
when did Dennings retire?

07:48.990 --> 07:51.340
He announced it a few days ago,
right after you were here.

07:51.383 --> 07:52.689
It was all pretty sudden.

07:52.733 --> 07:55.126
♪♪

07:55.170 --> 07:57.172
Did he say why?

07:57.215 --> 08:00.523
No, it's, uh, something
personal, I-I think.

08:00.567 --> 08:03.439
So, anyway, with everyone
shifting around,

08:03.483 --> 08:05.615
I need to fill
some key positions.

08:05.659 --> 08:07.530
What would you say
about stepping in

08:07.574 --> 08:09.619
to teach my elective
arts class?

08:09.663 --> 08:12.448
Y-You want me to teach?

08:12.492 --> 08:15.277
You'd be a natural,
and it's a dream gig.

08:15.320 --> 08:17.801
You wake up early
and get paid almost nothing.

08:17.845 --> 08:19.716
Oh, my God.
USC just posted.

08:19.760 --> 08:21.849
Uh, Dre, I gotta
call you back.

08:21.892 --> 08:23.807
I'm about to find out
if Tyrell got into USC.

08:23.851 --> 08:25.026
Tell him
I said good luck.

08:25.069 --> 08:26.114
And let me know
about the teaching.

08:26.157 --> 08:27.419
Let's get both of you
in school.

08:27.463 --> 08:28.986
W-W-We -- We will talk.

08:29.030 --> 08:30.422
Okay.

08:30.466 --> 08:32.686
Rome: Wait.
Let me get my camera.

08:32.729 --> 08:35.427
♪♪

08:35.471 --> 08:37.038
Regina: Oh, my God.
Here she comes again.

08:38.866 --> 08:41.738
That woman terrifies me
more than my Great Aunt Tabby

08:41.782 --> 08:44.175
who used to look directly
at whatever part

08:44.219 --> 08:46.526
of my pre-teen body
I was most self-conscious about

08:46.569 --> 08:47.527
when she spoke to me.

08:47.570 --> 08:49.572
Yikes.

08:49.616 --> 08:51.182
Will you handle her?

08:51.226 --> 08:52.357
Of course.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.012
Hi, Mrs. Jeffries.

08:55.056 --> 08:56.753
This is
the shrimp pasta?

08:56.797 --> 08:58.581
Yep.
And it's all the best quality.

08:58.625 --> 09:00.583
We were first at the fish market
this morning.

09:00.627 --> 09:02.019
And the seafood
croquettes?

09:02.063 --> 09:03.238
Right there.

09:03.281 --> 09:05.632
We love
the "Under the Sea" theme.

09:05.675 --> 09:07.329
I can't believe
you were able

09:07.372 --> 09:09.331
to make all of this
gluten-free.

09:09.374 --> 09:11.725
Uh, when we spoke
on the phone,

09:11.768 --> 09:13.727
you mentioned
the cashew allergy,

09:13.770 --> 09:15.598
but you never said
anything about gluten.

09:15.642 --> 09:17.208
I most certainly did.

09:17.252 --> 09:20.560
My husband has a terrible
allergy to wheat.

09:20.603 --> 09:22.170
No, I...

09:22.213 --> 09:24.346
There must've been
a misunderstanding.

09:24.389 --> 09:27.741
At Starting Fresh, we take
allergens very seriously.

09:27.784 --> 09:29.743
I'm sure you thought
you told us.

09:29.786 --> 09:32.267
Maybe we could whip up something
else special just for him?

09:32.310 --> 09:33.877
Are you kidding?

09:33.921 --> 09:35.923
His entire family
will be there

09:35.966 --> 09:38.316
and half of them have
the same allergy,

09:38.360 --> 09:40.710
which I clearly stated
on the phone.

09:40.754 --> 09:43.234
There is no way that I am paying
for any of this.

09:43.278 --> 09:44.714
What?

09:44.758 --> 09:47.064
And you should find
an employee

09:47.108 --> 09:49.066
who knows how
to do their job.

09:49.110 --> 09:50.981
[ Scoffs ]

09:51.025 --> 09:53.636
Okay. This?

09:55.725 --> 09:57.118
What? No.

09:57.161 --> 09:58.554
I made that for Grandpa.
We have to keep it.

09:58.598 --> 10:00.730
Okay, w-we can't keep
everything, Danny.

10:00.774 --> 10:03.037
We're trying
to empty the house.

10:03.080 --> 10:04.604
And what is this
even supposed to be?

10:04.647 --> 10:07.128
The hope and optimism
of a 6-year-old?

10:08.433 --> 10:10.392
Or maybe it's
a macaroni airplane --

10:10.435 --> 10:11.785
it's subjective.

10:11.828 --> 10:14.178
Okay, fine, be a hoarder.

10:14.222 --> 10:16.920
So just because I don't want to
put all of our family's memories

10:16.964 --> 10:18.008
in the trash,
I'm a hoarder?

10:19.444 --> 10:20.881
I don't want to be
doing this anyway.

10:20.924 --> 10:22.883
I wanted to spend
my last day here with Milo.

10:22.926 --> 10:25.668
Okay, wow, I'm so sorry
I'm asking you to do a fraction

10:25.712 --> 10:27.670
of what I'm gonna have to do
when the house sells,

10:27.714 --> 10:29.411
while you and Mom
are gallivanting

10:29.454 --> 10:30.978
across the French
countryside.

10:31.021 --> 10:32.675
We are not gallivan--

10:32.719 --> 10:34.111
Wait. Keep.

10:34.155 --> 10:35.765
What? No. W-We have a zillion
family photos,

10:35.809 --> 10:37.549
and I look like a zombie
in this one.

10:37.593 --> 10:39.639
Don't you remember that month
Dad and I went around

10:39.682 --> 10:41.684
putting it in random frames
all over the house

10:41.728 --> 10:43.338
just to bug you?

10:43.381 --> 10:44.905
[ Chuckles ]Yeah, you might be
surprised to learn

10:44.948 --> 10:47.429
that the month you tortured me
with an ugly photo of myself

10:47.472 --> 10:48.386
is not a fond memory.

10:48.430 --> 10:49.823
[ Chuckles ]

10:51.433 --> 10:52.477
What's this?

10:52.521 --> 10:54.044
What?

10:54.088 --> 10:56.656
"Look in the land
of green giants"?

10:58.440 --> 11:00.834
I-I think it's a clue from one
of those scavenger hunts

11:00.877 --> 11:02.966
Dad used to make us.

11:03.010 --> 11:04.620
[ Chuckles ]
He must've put it there

11:04.664 --> 11:07.275
thinking we'd move
the photo again.

11:07.318 --> 11:09.886
That was the summer
you went away to camp.

11:09.930 --> 11:12.062
W-We stopped messing
with the photo,

11:12.106 --> 11:13.281
and we never found it.

11:14.543 --> 11:16.588
Do you think whatever treasure
Dad hid for us

11:16.632 --> 11:18.199
is still around here
somewhere?

11:21.376 --> 11:23.726
Meetra: Yeah, I can see
that you wanted a scorpion.

11:23.770 --> 11:26.903
Totally.
It'll be about like four hours.

11:26.947 --> 11:28.644
Just surprising Greta
with lunch!

11:28.688 --> 11:30.211
Wait, she's --

11:30.254 --> 11:32.648
♪ I swam with you

11:32.692 --> 11:34.519
Greta: You cannot
drop by unannounced.

11:34.563 --> 11:36.304
It's totally
inappropriate!

11:38.262 --> 11:40.003
Katherine.

11:40.047 --> 11:43.659
Hey, uh, I just
dropped by with lunch,

11:43.703 --> 11:46.401
but you're busy
so, uh, I'll come back.

11:46.444 --> 11:47.924
No, uh,
Katherine, um...

11:49.534 --> 11:52.494
This -- This is
my, u-uh...

11:52.537 --> 11:54.626
I'm Julia.
Her wife.

11:54.670 --> 11:58.805
♪♪

12:03.287 --> 12:05.507
Julia was just ambushing me
to tell me

12:05.550 --> 12:07.204
she needs to sell our condo
right now,

12:07.248 --> 12:09.250
and if I want to buy her out,
she needs market value,

12:09.293 --> 12:11.252
even though we're not
supposed to be selling

12:11.295 --> 12:13.558
until after
the divorce is final.

12:13.602 --> 12:14.951
The market is on fire.

12:14.995 --> 12:17.127
Our neighborhood
has tripled in price,

12:17.171 --> 12:18.781
and I want my share now.

12:18.825 --> 12:20.957
That is not
what we agreed to.

12:21.001 --> 12:23.351
I-I know --You know, I see disputes
like this all the time.

12:23.394 --> 12:24.961
I'm a real estate
lawyer.

12:25.005 --> 12:27.355
And, um, there are agreements
that can be worked out.

12:27.398 --> 12:29.574
See, even
your new girlfriend

12:29.618 --> 12:31.011
thinks you are being
unreasonable.

12:31.054 --> 12:32.926
N-No, no, I don't.

12:32.969 --> 12:35.319
You cannot just expect
that you say sell and we sell.

12:35.363 --> 12:37.321
[ Scoffs ]
Oh, my God, I forgot.

12:37.365 --> 12:39.976
We always have to do things
your way.

12:40.020 --> 12:41.848
Well, when my way's
the right way, yes, we do.

12:41.891 --> 12:43.023
This is not
the right way!

12:43.066 --> 12:44.546
I'm telling you
we're gonna make money.

12:44.589 --> 12:47.201
But it's not what we agreed to,
at a more rational time,

12:47.244 --> 12:49.159
when we talked to each other
in a more civil way

12:49.203 --> 12:51.161
than you showing up
at my office.

12:51.205 --> 12:54.034
[ Men at Work's
"Down Under" plays ]

12:54.077 --> 12:56.514
♪ Where women glow
and men plunder ♪

12:56.558 --> 12:58.038
Hi. [ Chuckles ]

12:58.081 --> 13:00.344
Hi.
What's your name?

13:00.388 --> 13:01.519
Uh, Cate with a C.

13:01.563 --> 13:03.043
Cate.

13:03.086 --> 13:05.349
Uh, my parents took me
to your concert at the Forum

13:05.393 --> 13:06.611
on my 8th birthday.

13:06.655 --> 13:07.961
Wow.

13:08.004 --> 13:10.398
That must've been, what,
12 years ago now?

13:10.441 --> 13:12.400
18 years ago,
almost exactly.

13:12.443 --> 13:14.184
Right. Oof.

13:14.228 --> 13:15.620
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:15.664 --> 13:17.100
Uh, just so you know,

13:17.144 --> 13:19.450
my husband and I pray for you
all the time.

13:19.494 --> 13:22.714
We were really sorry
to hear about your accident.

13:22.758 --> 13:24.325
Oh! Oh.

13:24.368 --> 13:26.370
Really, um, I'm fine,
but thank you.

13:26.414 --> 13:28.111
Thanks. [ Chuckles ]Have a good one.

13:28.155 --> 13:29.852
♪♪

13:29.896 --> 13:31.941
♪ He just smiled and gave me
a Vegemite sandwich ♪

13:31.985 --> 13:33.203
Hi.

13:33.247 --> 13:34.683
♪ And he said

13:34.726 --> 13:35.902
♪ I come
from a land down under ♪Woman: Colin Hay?

13:35.945 --> 13:38.818
Oh, my God!
I love Men at Work!

13:38.861 --> 13:40.950
Regina: What kind of person
refuses to pay?

13:40.994 --> 13:43.779
It's gonna take us our next
three jobs to make up for this.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.520
And not to mention
she lied.

13:45.563 --> 13:48.392
She's a liar.
Lied right to our faces.

13:48.436 --> 13:51.656
Gina, I-I have to show you
something.

13:52.788 --> 13:54.355
[ Sniffles ]

13:54.398 --> 13:55.791
She was right.

13:57.401 --> 14:01.318
It wasmy fault.
I -- I'm so, so sorry.

14:01.362 --> 14:05.888
♪♪

14:05.932 --> 14:07.890
"Land of
the green giants."

14:07.934 --> 14:09.544
Where else
could that be?

14:09.587 --> 14:11.546
God, the expiration date
on some of these

14:11.589 --> 14:14.375
is probably older than
the treasure we are looking for.

14:14.418 --> 14:17.117
How many cans of cranberry sauce
does one actually need?

14:17.160 --> 14:19.510
One.
On Thanksgiving.

14:19.554 --> 14:22.122
Another thing I missed
being in France.

14:22.165 --> 14:23.558
[ Sighs ]

14:23.601 --> 14:25.386
Well,
are you and Milo

14:25.429 --> 14:27.301
gonna keep seeing each other
long distance?

14:27.344 --> 14:29.085
Yeah, he's gonna visit.

14:29.129 --> 14:31.044
And we're gonna try
to make things work.

14:31.087 --> 14:33.698
And if he cheats
on me again,

14:33.742 --> 14:35.439
at least we'll be
guillotine-adjacent.

14:35.483 --> 14:37.267
[ Chuckles ]

14:37.311 --> 14:39.922
Oh, my God.
I found it.

14:39.966 --> 14:42.272
"Never mix
red and white"?

14:42.316 --> 14:44.622
The wine rack.

14:44.666 --> 14:46.407
[ Men at Work's
"Who Can It Be Now?" plays ]

14:46.450 --> 14:48.452
♪ Who can it be now?

14:50.672 --> 14:52.456
Eddie: Come on, Anna.
Text me back.

14:52.500 --> 14:54.197
♪ At my door

14:54.241 --> 14:56.025
♪ Make no sound

14:56.069 --> 14:57.897
♪ Tiptoe across the floor

14:57.940 --> 14:59.028
Can you sign it
"to my biggest fan"?

14:59.072 --> 15:01.988
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, my goodness.

15:02.031 --> 15:04.251
Where did you
find this?

15:04.294 --> 15:05.556
The Internet.

15:05.600 --> 15:07.515
Oh, boy.

15:07.558 --> 15:09.473
Hello, from 2012.

15:09.517 --> 15:11.606
Rome: Okay, now let me just get
B cam up and running.

15:11.649 --> 15:13.434
Dude,
you're taking forever.

15:13.477 --> 15:15.175
I don't even care
if we film this.

15:15.218 --> 15:17.481
If I don't capture this moment,
your mom's gonna kill me.

15:17.525 --> 15:18.874
I applied
to five schools.

15:18.918 --> 15:20.267
Are you gonna do this
for every one?

15:20.310 --> 15:21.442
Oh, oh, yeah, yeah.

15:21.485 --> 15:22.922
And when you do
your touchdown dance,

15:22.965 --> 15:24.619
cheat to the left
and catch that light, okay?

15:24.662 --> 15:27.622
[ Chuckles ]
And action!

15:27.665 --> 15:29.015
[ Exhales deeply ]

15:31.017 --> 15:32.844
[ Sighs ]

15:36.587 --> 15:40.113
"We regret to inform you
that you have not been accepted

15:40.156 --> 15:42.550
for admission to --

15:42.593 --> 15:45.335
to the University
of Southern California."

15:45.379 --> 15:52.908
♪♪

15:52.952 --> 15:54.475
O-Okay, that--
that's just one.

15:54.518 --> 15:57.957
USC was my sure thing.

16:00.089 --> 16:01.047
[ Sighs ]

16:01.090 --> 16:03.310
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

16:05.355 --> 16:07.967
It's my mom.

16:08.010 --> 16:09.794
What am I gonna tell her?

16:11.622 --> 16:15.191
Can you s-stop
the cameras, please?

16:15.235 --> 16:21.676
♪♪

16:25.897 --> 16:28.596
So, uh, what do you think
our kid's gonna be like?

16:28.639 --> 16:29.814
Hmm.

16:29.858 --> 16:31.033
Perfect, probably?

16:31.077 --> 16:32.643
They'll love the Bruins.

16:32.687 --> 16:35.255
And music,
except techno.

16:35.298 --> 16:36.908
Yeah, and they'll be
super funny.

16:36.952 --> 16:39.737
Yeah, they'll bring the world
together in harmonious unity.

16:39.781 --> 16:42.044
Which will be easy 'cause
they'll be the President of
the United States of America.

16:42.088 --> 16:43.176
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

16:43.219 --> 16:44.873
What else do we have
on our vision board?

16:44.916 --> 16:47.528
Astronaut?
Olympian?

16:47.571 --> 16:49.182
Honestly?

16:51.923 --> 16:53.751
I just hope
they're happy.

16:53.795 --> 16:55.579
Yeah.

16:55.623 --> 16:57.755
Happy sounds good
to me.

16:57.799 --> 17:00.497
[ Door opens ]Hey, there!

17:00.541 --> 17:02.630
We haven't had any sex!

17:02.673 --> 17:04.632
Ah!
That's great.

17:04.675 --> 17:06.503
Yeah, and, y-you know,
if, uh --

17:06.547 --> 17:09.419
if today doesn't work,
I have an opening tomorrow.

17:09.463 --> 17:11.204
Of course he does.

17:11.247 --> 17:13.293
Alright.

17:13.336 --> 17:16.948
Let's see how things are going
with my favorite couple.

17:16.992 --> 17:19.081
Ha, I bet you say that
to all the couples.

17:19.125 --> 17:20.952
Oh, no.

17:20.996 --> 17:23.129
The couple I just saw
is the worst.

17:23.172 --> 17:25.305
You do not want to end up
in a Gymboree class with them.

17:25.348 --> 17:26.915
Trust me.

17:26.958 --> 17:28.656
Okay. [ Sighs ]

17:28.699 --> 17:30.266
Yeah?Maggie: Mm.

17:31.963 --> 17:36.229
Okay.
These are Maggie's eggs.

17:36.272 --> 17:39.101
I gotta say...

17:40.537 --> 17:42.235
...they look like they're in
the perfect spot today, guys.

17:46.108 --> 17:48.371
As in, you can go home
and have sex.

17:48.415 --> 17:49.851
♪♪

17:49.894 --> 17:51.418
[ Laughs ]Time out. Hold up.

17:51.461 --> 17:53.246
Go homeand have sex?

17:53.289 --> 17:55.770
For $135, I thought
we'd have a deluxe suite

17:55.813 --> 17:57.554
with some fertility idols,

17:57.598 --> 17:59.991
a private performance
from Kenny G. --

18:00.035 --> 18:02.733
The G stands for
"Gary, shut it."

18:02.777 --> 18:04.518
Let's go make a baby.

18:04.561 --> 18:05.997
Yes, ma'am.

18:06.041 --> 18:08.043
[ Eddie sighs ]

18:08.087 --> 18:09.871
Thank God the free cake
is distracting him

18:09.914 --> 18:11.307
from the fact
that I have no fans.

18:11.351 --> 18:13.353
What are you talking about?
It's a mob out there.

18:13.396 --> 18:14.789
Yeah, for Colin Hay.

18:14.832 --> 18:17.139
From Men at Work?
He's here?

18:17.183 --> 18:18.445
Cool!

18:18.488 --> 18:20.055
The entire line was singing
"Land Down Under"

18:20.099 --> 18:22.057
in harmony
most of the morning.

18:22.101 --> 18:23.450
I feel like such a poser.

18:23.493 --> 18:25.234
Hey, I've seen you
play stadiums.

18:25.278 --> 18:27.454
Yeah, now you've seen me
in the break room

18:27.497 --> 18:29.412
of a hotel Marriott,
so...

18:29.456 --> 18:31.675
rock star full circle.

18:31.719 --> 18:33.503
Eddie, people have taken time
out of their lives

18:33.547 --> 18:34.678
to get your autograph.

18:34.722 --> 18:36.724
That's the real deal.

18:36.767 --> 18:39.466
Well, I'm glad
you two think so.

18:39.509 --> 18:40.641
Thanks for bringing him.

18:40.684 --> 18:42.077
Of course.

18:42.121 --> 18:44.471
Where's Anna?

18:44.514 --> 18:46.821
Uh, she ran into Peter
last night.

18:46.864 --> 18:48.605
Oh, wow.

18:48.649 --> 18:50.738
Is she okay?
I don't know.

18:50.781 --> 18:52.783
She seemed pretty rattled,

18:52.827 --> 18:54.959
and I haven't been able
to talk to her all day.

18:55.003 --> 18:56.744
I'm a little worried,
to be honest.

18:56.787 --> 18:58.180
Hey, listen, um,

18:58.224 --> 19:01.357
I'm really sorry for what I said
at game night.

19:01.401 --> 19:03.185
I overstepped.

19:03.229 --> 19:06.188
Thank you.
I appreciate it.

19:06.232 --> 19:08.234
You know, it's a lot of pressure
meeting the ex-wife.

19:08.277 --> 19:09.670
Tell me about it.

19:09.713 --> 19:12.847
I just met Greta's ex-wife,
Julia, earlier.

19:12.890 --> 19:14.979
She was upsettingly
gorgeous.

19:15.023 --> 19:17.765
Oh, well, now you know
how Greta felt when she met me.

19:17.808 --> 19:20.289
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, well...

19:20.333 --> 19:22.291
Do you remember when
our therapist said

19:22.335 --> 19:24.293
that when couples are
passionate enough to fight,

19:24.337 --> 19:26.730
it means they have
something to fight for?

19:26.774 --> 19:28.906
Yeah, it's when they don't
care enough to fight

19:28.950 --> 19:30.560
that you know it's over.
Why?

19:30.604 --> 19:33.955
Well, the way Greta and her ex
cared enough to be fighting,

19:33.998 --> 19:35.086
it felt like I was looking at
two people

19:35.130 --> 19:37.567
five minutes away
from make-up sex.

19:37.611 --> 19:40.004
Look, you and Greta
seem like

19:40.048 --> 19:42.006
you have a really good thing
going on.

19:42.050 --> 19:44.618
Just don't overthink it.

19:44.661 --> 19:46.228
I guess you're right.

19:46.272 --> 19:48.230
Happens once a year.
Would you like my autograph?

19:48.274 --> 19:49.405
Huh?

19:49.449 --> 19:52.191
♪♪

19:52.234 --> 19:53.975
Hey.

19:54.018 --> 19:55.803
Don't want
to talk about it.

19:55.846 --> 19:57.413
Yeah, I know.

19:57.457 --> 19:58.980
But this is one of those
parenting moments

19:59.023 --> 20:00.677
where what I think
is best for you

20:00.721 --> 20:02.244
overrides what you think
is best for you.

20:02.288 --> 20:03.419
So scooch.

20:03.463 --> 20:05.769
[ Sighing ] Fine.

20:05.813 --> 20:08.555
Let the parenting pep talk
commence.

20:08.598 --> 20:09.991
Hm.
[ Sighs ]

20:11.775 --> 20:14.213
Rejection sucks.

20:14.256 --> 20:17.128
And nobody gets that more than
a guy who's in an industry

20:17.172 --> 20:20.654
where "well told"
still means a big fat no.

20:20.697 --> 20:22.743
But it's not just
one rejection.

20:22.786 --> 20:24.658
If I didn't get
into my safety,

20:24.701 --> 20:27.487
there's no way I'm getting
into my first choice.

20:28.879 --> 20:30.881
Yale posted.

20:30.925 --> 20:33.275
And I'm scared to hit that
button because until I do,

20:33.319 --> 20:36.670
I can still at least pretend
like I might have a future.

20:41.805 --> 20:44.634
Y-You remember what you told
Gina when Someday closed?

20:46.332 --> 20:47.811
You said, "Sometimes,
the worst things in life

20:47.855 --> 20:50.031
lead to
the best things."

20:50.074 --> 20:51.206
And I'm -- I'm not
gonna tell you

20:51.250 --> 20:54.035
that every cloud has
a silver lining.

20:54.078 --> 20:57.430
That path in front of you
is going to twist and turn

20:57.473 --> 21:00.215
in thousands of ways
that you're not expecting.

21:00.259 --> 21:04.654
But what matters
is how yourespond.

21:04.698 --> 21:08.049
If Yale's not
your next four years,

21:08.092 --> 21:11.139
we'll figure
something else out.

21:11.182 --> 21:12.923
'Cause Yale doesn't dictate
your future.

21:15.361 --> 21:17.319
You do.

21:17.363 --> 21:22.063
♪♪

21:22.106 --> 21:23.282
Okay.

21:24.674 --> 21:26.023
Okay.

21:26.067 --> 21:27.242
Let's do it.

21:27.286 --> 21:28.548
Hold on.
Let me get the camera.

21:28.591 --> 21:31.202
♪♪

21:31.246 --> 21:32.334
[ Camera beeps ]

21:32.378 --> 21:35.250
And action.

21:37.383 --> 21:38.906
I don't know
what happened.

21:38.949 --> 21:40.690
I must've just focused
on the cashews

21:40.734 --> 21:41.865
and totally missed
the gluten note.

21:41.909 --> 21:43.476
I'm such an idiot.

21:43.519 --> 21:45.913
My stupid mistake cost us
that whole job.

21:47.131 --> 21:49.264
Everyone's made them.

21:49.308 --> 21:51.875
I've made a thousand of them
myself.

21:53.747 --> 21:56.706
She's right about
the other thing, too.

21:56.750 --> 21:59.448
You should find someone else
to do this with.

21:59.492 --> 22:00.884
Don't want to.

22:00.928 --> 22:02.495
Not gonna.

22:02.538 --> 22:04.105
The integrity
you just showed

22:04.148 --> 22:06.194
is exactly why I want
to work with you.

22:06.237 --> 22:07.978
You could've said
nothing,

22:08.022 --> 22:10.416
let me keep blaming
that truly awful woman,

22:10.459 --> 22:11.895
but you didn't.

22:11.939 --> 22:15.290
You owned your mistake
and apologized.

22:16.857 --> 22:18.380
I'd rather have
someone I trust

22:18.424 --> 22:20.817
than someone with
all the experience in the world.

22:23.429 --> 22:25.387
Man: Oh, wow.

22:25.431 --> 22:26.867
They never have food trucks
in this neighborhood.

22:26.910 --> 22:28.608
Are you guys open?

22:30.261 --> 22:33.221
Um, yes,
actually, we are.Great.

22:33.264 --> 22:35.745
We've got seafood croquettes,
best in Boston.

22:35.789 --> 22:37.268
Great.
Uh, how much?

22:37.312 --> 22:38.966
Uh, $4?

22:39.009 --> 22:41.969
Forone order of them?

22:42.012 --> 22:43.187
$8.

22:43.231 --> 22:44.798
Okay.

22:44.841 --> 22:46.843
I'll take two orders.

22:46.887 --> 22:49.933
Excellent. Alright.
Let's do this.

22:49.977 --> 22:51.979
We looked at every
wine bottle.

22:52.022 --> 22:54.416
There's nothing here.

22:54.460 --> 22:57.201
Well, at least we can get
really, really drunk.

22:57.245 --> 22:59.421
Thanks, Dad.
[ Chuckles ]

23:02.642 --> 23:04.818
"Never mix
red and white."

23:04.861 --> 23:07.821
This is a pretty sophisticated
clue

23:07.864 --> 23:10.693
for an 8-
and 5-year-old.

23:10.737 --> 23:12.173
But wait.

23:12.216 --> 23:15.176
Do you remember when you put
your Shazam Underoos

23:15.219 --> 23:17.178
in the wash with
my first communion dress?

23:17.221 --> 23:19.789
[ Chuckles ]
You were so mad.

23:19.833 --> 23:21.008
But, you know,
at least we could

23:21.051 --> 23:22.618
pick you out of the crowd
at church.

23:22.662 --> 23:24.881
Yeah, the only pink
in a sea of white.

23:26.274 --> 23:28.450
Ohh!
"Never mix red and white."

23:28.494 --> 23:30.017
There he is.
Yeah. Okay.

23:30.060 --> 23:37.546
♪♪

23:37.590 --> 23:38.765
Oh!

23:38.808 --> 23:44.597
♪♪

23:44.640 --> 23:46.294
Oh, my God.
That's it!

23:46.337 --> 23:50.037
♪♪

23:50.080 --> 23:52.039
Wait, wait, wait.
That's --

23:52.082 --> 23:53.867
That's Dad's handwriting.

23:55.390 --> 23:57.436
That's Dad's thumbprint.

23:57.479 --> 24:02.702
♪♪

24:02.745 --> 24:07.837
♪♪

24:12.102 --> 24:13.364
Ready?Yeah.

24:13.408 --> 24:16.759
♪♪

24:16.803 --> 24:20.633
One root beer
and two straws.

24:20.676 --> 24:22.417
Oh, wait.
There's something else.

24:22.461 --> 24:29.859
♪♪

24:29.903 --> 24:32.253
[ Sighs ]
"Congratulations!

24:32.296 --> 24:34.037
You two found
the treasure,

24:34.081 --> 24:36.083
and because
you worked together,

24:36.126 --> 24:38.041
you get to share
an entire root beer."

24:38.085 --> 24:39.608
[ Chuckles ]

24:39.652 --> 24:42.306
"Sophie, I know
Danny chews way too loud

24:42.350 --> 24:44.091
and that
grosses you out,

24:44.134 --> 24:46.310
but we can't make him eat alone
in the hallway.

24:46.354 --> 24:48.617
Danny, I know Sophie steals
your Halloween candy

24:48.661 --> 24:50.140
out of your bucket,

24:50.184 --> 24:52.839
but you can't hide her
guitar picks in your Play-Doh."

24:52.882 --> 24:55.494
I only did that
like twice.

24:55.537 --> 24:58.279
"And it doesn't matter who
brushes their teeth the fastest.

24:58.322 --> 25:00.455
That is actually the opposite
of what you should be doing,

25:00.499 --> 25:02.544
and these races
have to stop.

25:05.895 --> 25:08.028
Danny, I want you to know
your mom and I decided

25:08.071 --> 25:10.247
to have a second child
because we knew

25:10.291 --> 25:13.076
our family wouldn't be
complete without you.

25:13.120 --> 25:15.078
And, Sophie, you probably
don't remember this,

25:15.122 --> 25:17.298
but when we brought him home
from the hospital,

25:17.341 --> 25:20.257
you wanted to sleep in the crib
with him to protect him.

25:20.301 --> 25:21.868
And when
we wouldn't let you,

25:21.911 --> 25:24.697
you set out your sleeping bag
on the floor next to him."

25:24.740 --> 25:26.263
You did that?

25:27.482 --> 25:29.179
I guess I did.

25:29.223 --> 25:31.181
[ Chuckles ]

25:31.225 --> 25:33.444
"One day, your mom and I
won't be here..."

25:36.056 --> 25:38.580
"...but you will always have
each other.

25:38.624 --> 25:40.582
The greatest gift
we could ever give you two

25:40.626 --> 25:41.931
is one another.

25:41.975 --> 25:43.411
Don't forget that.

25:43.454 --> 25:45.500
Love, Dad."

25:45.544 --> 25:51.332
♪♪

25:51.375 --> 25:57.468
♪♪

25:57.512 --> 25:58.905
[ Sighs ]

26:00.863 --> 26:03.779
It is so like her
to come in

26:03.823 --> 26:06.173
and just pull the rug out
from under me like that.

26:06.216 --> 26:08.088
That makes
my blood boil.

26:08.131 --> 26:09.872
I'm not selling.
It's the principle of it.

26:12.222 --> 26:14.790
I'm so sorry if she made you
feel uncomfortable.

26:14.834 --> 26:20.753
Um, to be honest,
it wasn't, uh, just her.

26:20.796 --> 26:22.755
It just seemed
like there's, uh,

26:22.798 --> 26:25.584
still a lot
of passion there.

26:25.627 --> 26:26.933
[ Chuckling ] No!

26:26.976 --> 26:28.543
It's not passion,
it's resentment.

26:28.587 --> 26:30.153
It's bad.

26:30.197 --> 26:31.720
You guys fought a lot?

26:31.764 --> 26:33.156
Yeah.

26:33.200 --> 26:34.854
Yeah, back when
we were first dating,

26:34.897 --> 26:36.812
I didn't know how to manage
my bipolar disorder,

26:36.856 --> 26:38.509
not like I do now.

26:38.553 --> 26:41.643
And it created a lot of chaos
and drama in my life.

26:41.687 --> 26:45.255
Which Julia fed off of.
I mean, it was toxic.

26:45.299 --> 26:47.867
Once I started listening
to my doctor,

26:47.910 --> 26:49.869
taking my meds,
and taking care of myself,

26:49.912 --> 26:53.568
I think she just
got bored with me.

26:53.612 --> 26:55.788
Well, just so you know,

26:55.831 --> 26:58.399
I like the new and improved
version of Greta.

26:58.442 --> 27:00.488
[ Chuckles ]
You sure?

27:00.531 --> 27:02.577
'Cause these days, all I want to
do is stay home and do puzzles.

27:02.621 --> 27:04.144
I love puzzles.

27:04.187 --> 27:06.407
[ Laughs ] That's why you're
exactly who I need.

27:06.450 --> 27:10.193
Someone who's patient
and reliable

27:10.237 --> 27:13.066
and someone who makes me
feel safe.

27:13.109 --> 27:17.200
♪♪

27:17.244 --> 27:21.422
Maybe it's time
to let go of this fight,

27:21.465 --> 27:23.250
find a new place
to live.

27:23.293 --> 27:25.687
And just let her win?

27:25.731 --> 27:28.081
You know, I'm, uh, not one
to toot my own horn,

27:28.124 --> 27:30.692
but, uh, some might say
you've already won.

27:30.736 --> 27:33.477
[ Laughs ]
Oh, yeah, alright.

27:33.521 --> 27:35.654
I mean, I -- I'd be
one of those people.

27:35.697 --> 27:37.003
I know.
Eddie's rubbing off onto me.

27:37.046 --> 27:38.787
I gotta stop.I like the confidence.

27:42.051 --> 27:43.749
[ Sighs ]

27:43.792 --> 27:46.665
Hey, hey, Colin Hay!

27:47.622 --> 27:48.797
I'm sorry.

27:48.841 --> 27:50.190
I sure you get that
all the time.

27:50.233 --> 27:51.452
Hi, I'm --

27:51.495 --> 27:54.498
Eddie -- Eddie Saville
from the Red Ferns.

27:54.542 --> 27:56.500
What, you -- you know
the Red Ferns?

27:56.544 --> 28:00.504
"Be My Katie," big song,
and a great song.

28:00.548 --> 28:01.854
Not always the case.

28:01.897 --> 28:03.246
[ Chuckles ]

28:03.290 --> 28:05.422
Well, the sax riff
from "Who Can It Be Now?"

28:05.466 --> 28:08.077
was the first thing I learned
in grade school band,

28:08.121 --> 28:10.123
and I couldn't stop
playing it.

28:10.166 --> 28:12.299
I know the feeling.
Gets in your head, that one.

28:14.736 --> 28:17.304
Can I ask you something?

28:17.347 --> 28:19.523
I get why I'm here,

28:19.567 --> 28:22.178
but why does Colin Hay do
something like this?

28:22.222 --> 28:24.485
With all of your success,
I would think,

28:24.528 --> 28:26.487
you know,
you wouldn't need to.

28:26.530 --> 28:28.881
Well, it's not a case of need,
is it?

28:28.924 --> 28:32.275
The truth is, these fans
have looked after me very well

28:32.319 --> 28:33.842
all these years.

28:33.886 --> 28:36.279
But I come here
for selfish reasons.

28:36.323 --> 28:40.980
Brings me joy, emotional
nourishment, human contact.

28:43.112 --> 28:45.680
Yeah, it's hard for me
to find joy in the fans

28:45.724 --> 28:50.076
when I can't find joy
in the music anymore.

28:50.119 --> 28:53.862
It's just hard to connect
with that guy.

28:53.906 --> 28:56.865
Sounds like you're trying
to connect to the wrong fella.

28:56.909 --> 28:59.302
You need to connect
with the guy who did it

28:59.346 --> 29:02.218
for the love of the music,
not just the applause.

29:02.262 --> 29:04.090
Hmm.

29:04.133 --> 29:07.876
♪♪

29:07.920 --> 29:08.877
I get it.

29:08.921 --> 29:09.878
No, it's hot, it's hot.
It is.

29:09.922 --> 29:11.532
But look, this may be

29:11.575 --> 29:13.882
the most important sex
we ever have,

29:13.926 --> 29:16.537
so I just --
I have to ask --

29:16.580 --> 29:17.973
is the shower definitely
off-limits?

29:18.017 --> 29:19.758
Where you're gonna hog
all the hot water

29:19.801 --> 29:20.497
and leave me
out in the cold?

29:20.541 --> 29:22.195
Forget it. No.

29:22.238 --> 29:24.719
It's missionary, and then I'm
gonna lie on my back for an hour

29:24.763 --> 29:26.895
with my hips raised
and my knees to my chest.

29:26.939 --> 29:29.115
I love it when you're boring
and bossy at the same time.

29:29.158 --> 29:30.116
[ Chuckles ]

29:30.159 --> 29:32.335
[ Knock on door ]

29:32.379 --> 29:34.729
You gotta be kidding me.

29:34.773 --> 29:36.775
10 bucks it's my dad.

29:36.818 --> 29:39.560
I told you, he can just sense
whenever I have a shot.

29:39.603 --> 29:40.779
[ Sighing ]
Oh, my God.

29:43.825 --> 29:46.132
Detective.

29:46.175 --> 29:48.830
I need to talk to you
about Peter Benoit.

29:48.874 --> 29:50.963
Okay, what lies
is that guy telling now?

29:51.006 --> 29:52.965
None.

29:53.008 --> 29:54.401
He's dead.

29:54.444 --> 29:58.666
♪♪

30:02.888 --> 30:05.194
Peter's cleaning lady
found him

30:05.238 --> 30:06.892
at the bottom of his stairs
this morning.

30:06.935 --> 30:08.981
No signs of forced entry,
so it was probably an accident.

30:09.024 --> 30:11.461
But I do have to
cover the bases,

30:11.505 --> 30:14.334
seeing as how he was attacked
not too long ago.

30:16.945 --> 30:19.252
You think she had
something to do with this?

30:19.295 --> 30:21.950
[ Sighs ]She's been with me
since yesterday.

30:21.994 --> 30:23.604
That's very funny.

30:23.647 --> 30:25.954
You're her alibi.
Got it.

30:25.998 --> 30:28.783
You got anybody
who can back that up?

30:28.827 --> 30:32.091
[ Sighs ]
We -- We were
at the doctor's earlier.

30:32.134 --> 30:34.093
We don't want anyone
to know.

30:34.136 --> 30:36.312
I'm gonna need
their information.

30:40.926 --> 30:42.710
[ Clears throat ]

30:42.753 --> 30:44.320
Going somewhere?

30:44.364 --> 30:46.540
Oh, uh, yeah,
we're moving in together.

30:46.583 --> 30:48.150
Today, actually.

30:48.194 --> 30:51.197
We were just about to start
loading up the car.

30:51.240 --> 30:52.633
I'm gonna need
the new address, as well.

30:56.028 --> 30:59.422
New address,
doc's name and number.

30:59.466 --> 31:00.859
Knock yourself out.

31:03.252 --> 31:04.863
I'll be in touch.

31:06.952 --> 31:09.519
[ Door opens, closes ]

31:09.563 --> 31:13.567
I can't believe he's dead,
after we just ran into him.

31:13.610 --> 31:15.395
It's crazy.

31:15.438 --> 31:16.918
I opened the door
and saw Saunders,

31:16.962 --> 31:18.789
I thought, "That's it.

31:18.833 --> 31:20.661
Peter finally
spilled the beans.

31:20.704 --> 31:22.619
I'm going to jail."

31:22.663 --> 31:24.404
[ Sighs ]

31:24.447 --> 31:25.971
After everything
he did to Sophie,

31:26.014 --> 31:28.451
is it wrong that
I'm glad he's gone?

31:30.105 --> 31:31.977
Oh, my God.

31:32.020 --> 31:33.239
Sophie.

31:35.937 --> 31:37.460
[ Sighs ]

31:37.504 --> 31:41.508
♪♪

31:41.551 --> 31:43.292
I think I already found
the perfect place.

31:43.336 --> 31:46.078
It's only a couple blocks
away from here.

31:46.121 --> 31:47.906
Uh...
Ah!

31:47.949 --> 31:49.255
That's too close,
isn't it?

31:49.298 --> 31:50.256
I freaked you out?

31:50.299 --> 31:51.692
[ Chuckles ]

31:51.735 --> 31:55.043
Actually,
I was thinking maybe...

31:55.087 --> 31:56.653
you know, since the schedule
is so tight,

31:56.697 --> 31:59.830
you could just stay here
for a bit

31:59.874 --> 32:01.876
until that place
is available.

32:04.357 --> 32:06.141
Are you sure?

32:06.185 --> 32:07.882
The only reason
I didn't ask you right away

32:07.926 --> 32:10.450
is 'cause I wanted
to check with Theo first,

32:10.493 --> 32:12.495
but he is very excited.

32:12.539 --> 32:14.019
[ Chuckles ] He is?

32:14.062 --> 32:16.021
Yeah, he's already pulling out
all the three-player games.

32:16.064 --> 32:17.892
He's tired of
the two-player games.

32:17.936 --> 32:19.328
[ Chuckles ]He said, "No offense, Mom."

32:19.372 --> 32:22.462
But, you know, to be honest,
some offense was taken.

32:22.505 --> 32:25.813
Well, I'd love to stay here
with you guys.

32:27.249 --> 32:28.772
You would?

32:28.816 --> 32:31.340
[ Sighs ]
I really would.

32:31.384 --> 32:35.518
♪♪

32:35.562 --> 32:36.867
What should we start with?

32:38.086 --> 32:41.263
T, I asked you to give me
a moment to ask her.

32:41.307 --> 32:43.265
I'm down for a classic
like Monopoly.

32:43.309 --> 32:45.137
Just to warn you both,

32:45.180 --> 32:47.617
I will own not only Park Place
andBoardwalk,

32:47.661 --> 32:49.097
but there will be
hotels.

32:49.141 --> 32:50.098
Multiple.

32:50.142 --> 32:51.360
Have fun with that.

32:51.404 --> 32:53.319
Everyone knows
it's all about the railroads.

32:53.362 --> 32:55.799
[ Laughs ] Is it?

32:55.843 --> 32:58.802
Here you go.Thanks so much.

32:58.846 --> 33:01.109
So sorry. We're sold out!

33:01.153 --> 33:02.589
[ Crowd groans ]

33:03.851 --> 33:05.635
We sold out!

33:05.679 --> 33:07.289
We made more money
parked here

33:07.333 --> 33:08.987
than we would've
on the catering job.

33:09.030 --> 33:09.988
Seriously?

33:10.031 --> 33:11.554
Yeah, like --
like a lot more.

33:11.598 --> 33:13.817
Thanks to you!

33:13.861 --> 33:16.168
I thought charging
$4 a croquette was crazy.

33:16.211 --> 33:18.387
I can't believe you upped it
to $10 by the end.

33:18.431 --> 33:19.954
Basic supply and demand,
baby.

33:19.998 --> 33:22.000
If the line's growing,
so are the prices.

33:22.043 --> 33:24.828
Hmm.
[ Laughs ]

33:24.872 --> 33:26.395
You know,
I sent my dad to Miami

33:26.439 --> 33:28.049
to patch things up
with his wife.

33:28.093 --> 33:31.052
He's basically just staying on
as a silent partner,

33:31.096 --> 33:35.448
which means I need a really,
really loud partner.

33:36.971 --> 33:39.278
I think
that's always been you.

33:39.321 --> 33:40.192
Are you sure?

33:40.235 --> 33:41.671
[ Chuckles ]

33:41.715 --> 33:43.456
Y-You guys put in
all the capital.

33:43.499 --> 33:44.674
Yeah, but I don't want to do
this alone.

33:44.718 --> 33:46.285
I never have.

33:49.505 --> 33:52.378
Hi, uh, will you guys be back
any time soon?

33:53.640 --> 33:55.033
Uh...

33:55.076 --> 33:56.121
yeah.

33:57.818 --> 33:59.559
Yeah, we'll be back.

33:59.602 --> 34:00.647
Awesome.

34:00.690 --> 34:03.606
[ Both chuckle ]

34:05.130 --> 34:06.783
I got in.

34:06.827 --> 34:08.046
I got -- I got in!

34:08.089 --> 34:10.048
I got it, I got it.
Wait, wait.

34:10.091 --> 34:11.223
I got in.
Come on!

34:11.266 --> 34:13.007
Yale, baby!
Yale, baby!

34:13.051 --> 34:15.227
New Haven, I'm coming for you.
I'm coming for you.

34:15.270 --> 34:18.360
Oh, my God.
You still editing that thing? They ain't gon' be ready
for me, Tyrell!

34:18.404 --> 34:20.710
You mean the video of my foster
son getting accepted into Yale?

34:20.754 --> 34:21.929
Yep.

34:21.972 --> 34:23.322
No, really,
I'm almost finished.

34:23.365 --> 34:24.758
Which means I can
almost get started

34:24.801 --> 34:26.107
on the extended
director's cut.

34:26.151 --> 34:28.153
[ Both chuckle ]

34:28.196 --> 34:31.721
You know, I couldn't have
done this without you.

34:31.765 --> 34:33.288
You were always gonna go
to college.

34:33.332 --> 34:34.681
Nothing was gonna get
in the way of that.

34:34.724 --> 34:38.032
Yeah, but you didn't just
help me get into college.

34:38.076 --> 34:40.469
You helped me figure out
who I wanted to be.

34:40.513 --> 34:42.167
[ Sighs ]

34:42.210 --> 34:44.995
I never thought my fairy
godmother would have a beard

34:45.039 --> 34:48.086
and be so...bald.

34:48.129 --> 34:50.436
You are gonna regret saying that
when I upload this

34:50.479 --> 34:52.655
and your goofy dance goes viral
on TikTok.

34:52.699 --> 34:54.701
[ Chuckles ] Okay.

34:54.744 --> 34:57.095
Well, I'm gonna go
tell my mom the good news.

34:57.138 --> 35:06.974
♪♪

35:07.017 --> 35:08.932
[ Ringing]

35:08.976 --> 35:10.238
Dre: Rome, hey!

35:10.282 --> 35:11.935
Hey, Dre.

35:11.979 --> 35:13.937
I've been thinking
about your offer.

35:13.981 --> 35:15.504
The timing
could not be worse,

35:15.548 --> 35:17.724
and I'm in no position
to take low pay,

35:17.767 --> 35:20.422
but I think I'm in,
man.

35:20.466 --> 35:21.684
Yes!

35:21.728 --> 35:24.383
[ Laughing ] Yes.

35:24.426 --> 35:27.255
♪♪

35:27.299 --> 35:28.909
[ Chuckles ]

35:28.952 --> 35:30.258
Oh.

35:30.302 --> 35:32.260
[ Laughs ]
It tastes like

35:32.304 --> 35:34.915
a grandma sitting
on an old couch.

35:34.958 --> 35:37.613
Should we try
the green beans next?

35:37.657 --> 35:39.615
[ Chuckles ] What, are you
trying to get botulism

35:39.659 --> 35:41.226
to avoid going back
to France?

35:41.269 --> 35:42.705
Maybe.

35:46.492 --> 35:47.971
You know, um...

35:48.015 --> 35:50.191
[ Sighs ]

35:50.235 --> 35:52.193
...I never had to worry
about Mom or Charlie

35:52.237 --> 35:54.761
because I knew that
you were with them.

35:54.804 --> 35:56.197
But it wasn't fair of me

35:56.241 --> 35:58.504
to let you shoulder
that whole burden alone.

36:00.070 --> 36:01.898
You were going through
a lot, too.

36:03.117 --> 36:05.380
Yeah,
but I'm good now.

36:05.424 --> 36:08.514
So I was thinking, um,

36:08.557 --> 36:12.518
maybe I could talk to Mom and
tell her you can live with me?

36:12.561 --> 36:13.954
If that's what you want.

36:16.261 --> 36:18.828
♪♪

36:18.872 --> 36:21.091
[ Chuckles ]
What, is this a yes?

36:21.135 --> 36:24.007
It's actually a no,
but thank you.

36:24.051 --> 36:26.227
Wait, really?
Are you sure?

36:26.271 --> 36:30.623
Today reminded me that I grew up
with a great older sibling,

36:30.666 --> 36:33.582
and I think Charlie
deserves that, too.

36:33.626 --> 36:36.368
Okay.
[ Chuckles ]

36:36.411 --> 36:39.414
But you have to promise me
that you'll both come back

36:39.458 --> 36:41.242
and eat the cranberry sauce
with me this Thanksgiving.

36:42.287 --> 36:43.853
Deal.
[ Chuckles ]

36:43.897 --> 36:46.116
Now,
if you'll excuse me,

36:46.160 --> 36:49.729
I have a mountain
of pasta-based artwork to pack.

36:51.470 --> 36:52.601
[ Chuckles ]

36:52.645 --> 37:00.870
♪♪

37:00.914 --> 37:09.270
♪♪

37:09.314 --> 37:17.496
♪♪

37:17.539 --> 37:18.888
[ Knock on door ]

37:21.108 --> 37:22.718
Hey.
Hey.

37:23.763 --> 37:25.678
What are you doing here?

37:25.721 --> 37:27.941
Soph, uh...

37:27.984 --> 37:29.551
I...

37:29.595 --> 37:30.509
[ Inhales deeply ]

37:30.552 --> 37:32.162
I need to tell you
something.

37:32.206 --> 37:35.165
♪♪

37:35.209 --> 37:36.906
[ Colin Hay's
"Beautiful World" plays ]

37:36.950 --> 37:38.299
There you go.

37:38.343 --> 37:41.128
♪ I like drinking Irish tea

37:41.171 --> 37:42.782
You're gonna need some ice
on that tonight.

37:42.825 --> 37:44.827
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, no kidding.

37:44.871 --> 37:46.307
We'll be doing this again
in a few months.

37:46.351 --> 37:47.787
Are you interested?

37:49.528 --> 37:51.921
♪ I like making my own tea

37:51.965 --> 37:53.096
You know what?[ Pen taps ]

37:53.140 --> 37:54.141
Hit me up.

37:54.184 --> 37:55.751
Will do.

37:55.795 --> 37:58.145
♪ My, my, my,
it's a beautiful world ♪

37:58.188 --> 38:01.322
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

38:01.366 --> 38:03.324
♪ I like driving in my car

38:03.368 --> 38:05.761
Hey!
How's my favorite rock star?

38:05.805 --> 38:07.197
Sophie:
Have you talked to Anna?

38:07.241 --> 38:08.982
No.

38:09.025 --> 38:11.027
I have been trying to get
in touch with her all day, why?

38:11.071 --> 38:13.291
Eddie, Peter's dead.

38:14.379 --> 38:16.032
Oh, my God.

38:17.991 --> 38:19.775
Anna?!

38:21.734 --> 38:22.865
Anna?

38:24.171 --> 38:26.478
Eddie, hey, hi.

38:26.521 --> 38:28.567
God. [ Sighs ]

38:28.610 --> 38:30.830
I'm sorry. I was just trying
to get ahold of you all day.

38:30.873 --> 38:33.267
I was worried.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.443
Oh, my God.
I'm so sorry.

38:35.487 --> 38:37.445
You know what?
I-I...

38:37.489 --> 38:38.751
I broke my phone.

38:40.927 --> 38:42.232
Have you heard
about Peter?

38:42.276 --> 38:44.104
Yeah, I did.

38:44.147 --> 38:47.499
Um, the police,
they called me this afternoon.

38:48.935 --> 38:50.458
You're doing okay?

38:50.502 --> 38:52.808
[ Sighs ] I'm fine.

38:54.375 --> 38:55.420
Come on in.

38:55.463 --> 38:56.899
I'll be right back.

38:56.943 --> 38:58.510
I was just gonna take
the trash out, so...

38:58.553 --> 39:01.034
Yeah.

39:01.077 --> 39:02.557
Okay.

39:02.601 --> 39:12.306
♪♪

39:12.350 --> 39:22.229
♪♪

39:22.272 --> 39:23.448
You hungry?

39:27.930 --> 39:31.064
You know, most people label
their boxes by the room.

39:31.107 --> 39:33.588
Gary has his boxes labeled
by importance?

39:33.632 --> 39:35.416
Who -- Who does that?

39:35.460 --> 39:37.984
Th--This one
says 4 out of 10.

39:38.027 --> 39:39.333
Where am I
supposed to put that?

39:39.377 --> 39:41.727
Anything six or below goes
in the back closet,

39:41.770 --> 39:43.206
leave seven or higher
out.

39:43.250 --> 39:45.295
Oh.

39:45.339 --> 39:46.688
Thank you,
Professor Howard.

39:46.732 --> 39:49.299
Ooh.
I'm not hating that.

39:50.910 --> 39:53.391
How did Sophie take the news
about Peter?

39:53.434 --> 39:55.218
Not great.
Mm.

39:55.262 --> 39:57.133
Yeah. I think she was
pretty overwhelmed.

39:57.177 --> 39:58.787
It's hard.

39:58.831 --> 40:01.094
Not being able
to get closure.

40:01.137 --> 40:05.925
I never believed in karma, but
maybe I need to rethink that.

40:10.625 --> 40:11.583
[ Sighs ]

40:11.626 --> 40:12.845
Saunders: Gary.

40:15.238 --> 40:16.196
Hey.

40:16.239 --> 40:17.589
You coming
to help me move?

40:17.632 --> 40:20.766
You can grab a box,
uh, rated six or lower

40:20.809 --> 40:23.246
and, you know,
lift with your knees.

40:23.290 --> 40:25.771
I spoke to your doctor.

40:25.814 --> 40:27.860
He corroborated
your story.

40:27.903 --> 40:29.775
And I just want to say
good luck.

40:31.559 --> 40:32.952
Thanks.

40:32.995 --> 40:34.432
Appreciate that.

40:34.475 --> 40:40.655
♪♪

40:40.699 --> 40:43.179
You good, man?Yep.

40:43.223 --> 40:46.574
♪♪

40:46.618 --> 40:49.795
I feel sorry for whatever
vegetables have to be processed

40:49.838 --> 40:51.971
in this pitiful excuse
for a processor.

40:52.014 --> 40:53.886
Don't be judgey, Gina.

40:53.929 --> 40:55.888
I make a mean hummus
in that thing.

40:55.931 --> 40:57.672
Must be a slow
and painful death

40:57.716 --> 40:59.500
for each and every one
of those chickpeas.

40:59.544 --> 41:02.503
It is Maggie's favorite hummus.
Isn't that right, Bloom?

41:02.547 --> 41:04.113
You know I love
a chunky hummus.

41:04.157 --> 41:05.332
[ Chuckles ]

41:06.768 --> 41:08.248
Why were you
at the doctor?

41:08.291 --> 41:09.554
What?

41:09.597 --> 41:10.642
I heard the detective.

41:10.685 --> 41:11.773
He said that you were
at the doctor,

41:11.817 --> 41:13.949
and then
he wished you luck.

41:15.385 --> 41:16.169
What's going on?

41:19.564 --> 41:22.523
Uh, yeah.
Well, uh, the truth is --

41:22.567 --> 41:24.394
We're trying
to have a baby.

41:24.438 --> 41:25.700
Regina: Ohh!

41:26.658 --> 41:27.746
Wait, you're...

41:27.789 --> 41:29.312
You...

41:29.356 --> 41:30.966
[ Laughs ]
Oh, stop it.Oh, my God. Yes!

41:31.010 --> 41:32.490
[ Grunts ]

41:32.533 --> 41:34.492
Man, I was worried.

41:34.535 --> 41:36.885
Yeah, you know.

41:36.929 --> 41:38.496
I'm getting you
a new food processor.

41:38.539 --> 41:41.281
That baby deserves to eat purees
that are actually pureed.

41:41.324 --> 41:42.456
[ Chuckles ]Gary: What is this?

41:42.500 --> 41:43.805
Do you want me to record
your reaction

41:43.849 --> 41:45.198
to us trying
to have a baby?

41:45.241 --> 41:46.591
No, no.

41:46.634 --> 41:49.071
I recorded
my foster son

41:49.115 --> 41:50.943
getting accepted to Yale
with this today.

41:50.986 --> 41:54.250
Hm?
Now I want you to have it.

41:54.294 --> 41:57.906
I want you to capture
all of the magic, okay?

41:57.950 --> 42:00.343
Not -- Not...

42:00.387 --> 42:02.258
Not allof the magic.

42:02.302 --> 42:04.913
How we fill this memory card
is entirely up to us.

42:04.957 --> 42:07.481
[ Sighs ]If it's a boy, name it Gene.

42:07.525 --> 42:09.048
If it's a girl, Gina.Got it.

42:09.091 --> 42:11.267
Give me some Iron Mike singing
"Twinkle Twinkle Little Star."

42:11.311 --> 42:12.486
[ High-pitched voice ]
♪ Twinkle, Twinkle

42:12.530 --> 42:14.183
[ Normal voice ] Stop.

42:14.227 --> 42:15.837
I'm gonna be an auntie!
I'm gonna be an auntie!

42:15.881 --> 42:17.665
We're having a baby!Rome's gonna change
the diapers!

